snippet.textDisplay: If anybody would like to see some genuinely good hamster care and DIY projects I suggest Erin's Animals or Victoria Raechel. Not that this isn't really impressive but the hamsters cage should be large (450sq inches minimum - hamsters don't benefit from levels so these don't count either), at least 6 inches of bedding (aspen wood shavings not sawdust, pine or cedar. Kaytee clean and cozy is a good bedding choice just as long as it is unscented). A dwarf hamster should have no less than an 8 inch solid wheel, and a Syrian should have no less than 12 inches of a solid wheel. Search online if you can't find these things in the pet store. The internet is full of good (and bad) resources for caring for hamsters. Generally, German hamster care is far superior as it encourages the hamsters natural instincts of burrowing and foraging. Also wire cages make it really easy for your hamster to escape so it is best to consider a glass aquarium or a plastic DIY bin cage. This will also allow you to see your hamster better. People might think "wtf it's just a hamster" but they are living beings too and if you really want them as a pet you should treat them like one. You wouldn't let your dogs suffer in subpar care would you?

snippet.textDisplay: I hate to be that person but your hamster cage should be minimum 450 square inches of floor space (not including levels or additional cages) so maybe you could upgrade your cage. The IKEA detolf is a fabulous example of a good cage (even though it's originally a shelving unit) or you could get an aquarium or build a bin cage (these should be very large) And your wheel should be solid (no wires or mesh as they can get injuries) and ensure it is at least 8 inches for a dwarf or 12 inches for a Syrian hamster. Please do some more research. It's great that you have built this separate play area but don't you think his main home should be larger than his play area?

snippet.textDisplay:
Things hamsters need:

bare minimum of continual floor space (levels and tubes don’t count) :450sq inches

multiple hides

bare minimum wheel: 6 inch solid (for this type of hamster, Syrians will need much larger)

areas where the bedding is around 6 inches deep for burrowing

multiple chew toys (their teeth constantly grow)

sand bath (use heat treated play sand or reptile sand, they can’t bathe in water, don’t use super fine sand or dust)

no hate, just advice to improve the life of hamsters! Clearly he cares about Jimothy if he’s willing to spend so much time and effort building a mansion play house for him 💚💚

(I only say this to improve the life of this ham based on what is seen in this video, he very well could be providing all of these things already)
